name: ALISHER
bio: [('Beginning', 'He began playing table tennis at age 12. (limon.kg, 25 Jan 2016)'), ('Reason', '"It all began with the fact that some houses began to clean their basements and we found a table tennis table. We took it out to the yard, after which we bought rackets and started playing. My brother and I got on well, and at that time there was a table tennis club at school. We signed up and slowly began to participate in city competitions." (limon.kg, 25 Jan 2016)'), ('Memorable', "Competing at the 2005 World Championships in Shanghai, People's Republic of China. (limon.kg, 25 Jan 2016)"), ('Additional Information', 'GeneralCOACHINGIn 2014 he began working as the coach of the Kyrgyzstan national male and junior table tennis teams. "When you work as a coach, you become a psychologist. There are times when your students are not feeling well, and you are for them as a senior companion, and maybe even as a dad, because you go with them to competitions." (Facebook profile, 28 Mar 2017; limon.kg, 25 Jan 2016)FOOTBALL VS TABLE TENNISHe took up football and table tennis simultaneously, before he decided to concentrate on table tennis. "I practiced two kinds of sports in parallel. But neither the one nor the other coach knew about it, that I combine two kinds of sports. Once, at a competition in the school sports days, which took place at the Physical Training Institute, I played table tennis, and the football coach came in. He saw that I was playing well, but at the same time he was angry because he was not aware that I was doing table tennis. On the next training session he told me \'decide whether it\'s football or table tennis\'." (limon.kg, 25 Jan 2016) '), ('Influence', 'His grandfather Yusup Musayev. (limon.kg, 25 Jan 2016)'), ('Education', 'Kyrgyz Russian Slavic University, Kyrgyzstan'), ('Languages', 'Russian'), ('Hobbies', 'Spending time with friends, going to the cinema, playing football. "In the 10th grade I realised that girls also wrestled and that there were regional competitions. I went there and that\'s how everything started." (itnsource.com, 04 Jun 2012)'), ('Debut', '2010 for Kyrgyzstan, Asian Games in Guangzhou, China (Athlete, 09 Aug 2016)'), ('Coach', 'Nurbek Izabekov [national, personal], KGZ (sport.gov.kg, 12 Jul 2018)'), ('Memorable', 'Winning bronze in the 55kg category at the 2014 Asian Games in Incheon, Republic of Korea. (Athlete, 09 Aug 2016)'), ('Awards', 'In 2013 and 2016 she was named one of the Best Athletes of the Year in Kyrgyzstan. (knews.kg, 18 Jan 2017; vb.kg, 24 Dec 2013)She has received the title of Master of Sport of International Class in Kyrgyzstan. (sport.gov.kg, 12 Jul 2018)'), ('Additional Information', 'GeneralNATIONAL FIRSTShe became the first female wrestler to represent Kyrgyzstan at the Olympic Games when she competed at the 2012 Games in London. She was ranked 13th in the 63kg category. (SportsDeskOnline, 15 Apr 2016; rus.azattyk.org, 20 Jul 2012)FURTHER EDUCATIONShe has studied at the Kyrgyz State Academy of Physical Education and Sport in Bishkek, Kyrgyzstan. (sport.gov.kg, 18 Jan 2018) '), ('Hero', 'Soviet weightlifter Kanybek Osmonaliyev, Russian pole vaulter Yelena Isinbayeva. (Athlete, 09 Aug 2016)'), ('Influence', 'Her family, and her coach. (Athlete, 09 Aug 2016)'), ('Injuries', 'She sustained a shoulder injury in 2017 and was unable to compete at the 2018 Asian Championships in Bishkek, Kyrgyzstan. name: EUGEN
bio: [('Beginning', 'He began cycling in Germany. (astanafans.com, 25 Apr 2009)'), ('Awards', 'In 2012 he was named one of the Best Athletes of the Year in Kyrgyzstan. (SportsDeskOnline, 09 Aug 2018)SUSPENSION:He tested positive for meldonium in March 2017 and was suspended for 15 months by the International Cycling Union [UCI].
